Daily menu of an obese child: not breakfast and dinner
More than one third of children aged 9-13 have overweight problems, where overweight affects 9 per cent of the school population and obesity 5 per cent.
Obese children originate in most families with an unhealthy lifestyle, according to current research.
It shows again the importance of the environment where it grows for a healthy development of the person, as well as the models that serve as a reference.
At the table, obsessive children are fed, for example, by sausages at least twice as often as children of families with normal weight.
For dinner, more than 19% of obese people had eaten fries the day before the analysis, which is linked to the prevention program " Obesity is not a coincidence".
In families of overweight children, there is no practice of sports, which applies to most current families, where only 15 per cent of children responded that their parents, at least once a week, find time for physical exercise.
Survey of 900 children
The survey was conducted at the end of last school year and took part in the same nearly 900 children of Basic Education throughout the Czech Republic.
It was already the second edition of the program of "The Obesity of Is Not a Chance", which supports the General Health Insurance Company and Unilever.
So far, more than 12,000 children have participated in the project from the 4th to the 8th course.
An adequate diet and quite family exercise are determining factors, which significantly decrease the number of children with overweight and even obesity.
"Only half of the children surveyed have responded that they have five meals per day according to the regime: breakfast, lunch, food, snack and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet," she picks up one of the survey results.
No breakfast but with a dining area
Experts warn that in healthy development, details are also important, such as having a set time for family breakfast.
In Czechia, however, only 23 per cent of schoolchildren's families have breakfast at the same time.
In most families, each one has breakfast alone.
But the worst thing was to find out that in 10% of households there is no breakfast.
Breakfast is, however, the basis of a proper daily diet.
The study shows that in families of obese children, healthy fries are consumed more frequently.
Almost all - regardless of weight - drink sweet refreshments daily (70%).
In general, more than 40 per cent of the children surveyed do sports, but among their parents, this result is reduced to less than half, only 15 per cent.
Make your diet
The next phase of the study enabled the chosen girls (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to create their own diets from all possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
"The food preferences of Czech children between 12 and 15 years of age, from the point of view of healthy nutrition, are far from ideal."
Among your favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets
"It is especially alarming the popularity of sweet refreshments," is advised in the final report of the study.
As the main food the palm is taken the pasta and follow closely the poultry meat.
Practically, children always reject vegetables and taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Switching to healthy habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they receive fair information.
"In the control group of the study participants, who filled in the questionnaire after the completion of the prevention programme " Obesity is not a coincidence", in many cases a major change was given in favour of the principles of healthy diet," the results of the study point out.
Call attention, for example, to sweet refreshments, where many children would begin to prefer normal and ordinary water.
Children would also choose in the questionnaire the poultry meat and fish for the main meal and would restrict the consumption of sweet food and flour derivatives.
