En Need for Speed: The Run competes all over America.
Review
A journey, initially unoccupied, is complicated because of a series of unwarranted neglects of a routine journey during the morning shift.
To some extent, expectations were met, but this is of no use, if, in fact, nothing extraordinary was intended to be done.
The new delivery, to which The Run is added, has aroused great expectations already before its premiere.
I promised I'd blow up the old Need for Speed racing saga and, as a result, it appears as a game that shouldn't end up being once again a genre of action without more.
We are also curious to know how the scenes would be inserted, where the main character comes down from the car and walks through his own foot.
As is usually the case in the NFS series, the results do not vary much in terms of what we expected.
There are careers that can be taken as acceptable, but in the total calculation points are lost due to absurd failures, which have been appearing in the series for years.
Actually, we cannot even call errors, but rather the incomprehensible distancing of programmers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are introduced into a story, whose protagonist, Jack, has certain personal problems; to solve them, you are offered to participate in an illegal career throughout America.
You sit at the wheel on the west coast, in San Francisco, and your mission is to get the first to New York.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than fifty races.
It follows that each race takes place on a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
In this way, one does not even remotely feel that the game always offers the same thing.
Some of the environments are even pleasant in sight, although the technical level of the graph is equivalent to that of previous deliveries of the series.
Therefore, it is nothing of the other world.
But the walk through the desert, the autumn landscape or the high snow-covered mountains produce a very pleasant visual effect.
In addition, the races are diversified from time to time by an atypical element.
Thus, for example, in the desert you find a sandstorm that decreases visibility.
On the other hand, in the mountains you must be careful not to bury an avalanche.
According to that, each of the races is well developed.
There's only a couple of models, but that's enough.
For a moment, you try to advance a number of rivals required (the normal one in a classic race), then try to make time (the classic timed duel) and then wait for a duel against a single opponent.
In the middle of all this the police sometimes appear, which only makes things even harder.
The novelty is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape someone and you have to help him, always pressing the button right at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are quite fewer landscapes in the game than might be expected (in particular there are only three).
But the final result is positive, because this element does not become annoying and, in the context already mentioned, it is one of the elements that make the game more interesting.
The driving model follows the footprints of previous episodes.
That means that today is no longer a big deal, but you can't say it's bad.
If you're looking for a realistic simulation, you can look elsewhere.
But a race designed with a lot of action suits this style of driving quite well, although we can find something better between the games of competition.
So far, everything's in order.
But problems arise after a certain time.
Unlike the correct driving models, the collisions are no longer the same.
Of games of this kind you can't expect it to create complicated deformations and collisions, but in fact before a blow against any object, you can't predict how your car will react, with which not everything is in order.
It is typical that, by making a very adjusted advance or circulating the car with a normal traffic, there are only slight rocks, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up making uncontrolled pirouettes.
Or it's completely destroyed.
Thanks to the restorative system, there are no big problems, but it can put you in a bad mood.
The resets are programmed in such a way that, when you suffer an accident or get off the track, the game returns you to the last point of rescue on the track.
However, in each race there are only five resets available.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it's no more than a help in case something goes wrong, but it's not much to trust.
Sometimes, not resecting helps, only helps you learn the given stage of memory.
A great disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, one must enter in a specific way; otherwise, they are impossible to take.
Other times you find yourself in some place "civil" vehicles always with the same configuration, even if you are the first, fifth or you arrived five minutes before or after.
This makes you angry above all in situations, when you see that two cars that go to the meeting in opposite directions, your opponent moves forward without any problems, but when you get there, you have to turn or either slow down.
It is the same when you arrive, because it is programmed that the "surprise" will always happen in front of your nose.
Opponents also have one more advantage.
Throughout the game you will reach places where, regardless of the moment, the same opponent will always advance you in the same place.
This also happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must arrive before you, at any price.
When it goes ahead of you, it makes it difficult for you to see the cars coming from the front, so at first you can make the car tick.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspense and adrenaline, but the execution is so apparent that it will certainly disappoint you immediately.
And it's a shame, because even if the travel model is simple, the game is fun and with action, so it's often not possible to follow the detail what happens or where.
And it really doesn't matter, if merit takes the idea with fifty exclusive tracks or the classification in the race so that it doesn't break boredom, or anything else.
An unusual idea is changing cars during the races.
You have to keep an eye on the gas station next to the road, because right there you have to switch cars, although in the vast majority of cases you will have enough of what you have.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports are suitable for urban areas, American strong cars for straight highways and over-sport exotics for technical driving, for example, by mountain roads with curves.
In addition, the main narrative thread also appears a thread of parallel challenges, that is, there are races in specific places that you will know about the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also points of experience for your profile, which serves both challenges and stories.
By reaching the top level, the driver opens up several possibilities, starting with the car and ending with backgrounds for the profile.
At the same time, an online Autolog function is connected, which compares your results with those of other players and provides other community functions.
One of the most difficult elements to understand is how the last race in history is made.
With the car you arrive to the subway tunnel (pass), where you start to run in darkness along the tracks (pass).
The speed meter marks you between 150 and 200 km/h (pass) and, suddenly, behind you comes the metro convoy and it takes you in front of you no more.
In the drafting we will certainly have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the programming of the game no one even thought a little or if the real authors take us for a bunch of fools.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the general visual effects result in most pleasant cases, sometimes even superb.
What a pity it is that, in the most tense moments, image quality is reduced and, sometimes, in a serious way.
This mainly affects accidents where many participants are involved, when image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In order to be of pleasure to most of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category "each of his father and his mother", but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game just for his music.
The final feeling of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore quite confused.
If the game avoided absolutely silly mistakes, we would have trouble claiming that The Run is the best NFS game in recent years.
It gives the feeling that the game is not finished.
The fun is assured, but prepared because the mistakes will hit you in the eyes with the force of some airport reflectors.
The choirs of the Carolina University will participate in the concert "Third Students".
The joint celebration of the International Student Day and the anniversary of the Third Revolution as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Festival Academic Party.
During the same period, twenty corals will be presented from secondary and university centres.
The festival revolves around two concerts on 17 November.
"The Carolina University has a high participation in the festival."
Among the current choirs are the coral of the Faculty of Pedagogy and the Faculty of Humanities, on the festival committee is the director Václav Hampl," said the organization's director, Jakub Čaloun.
The summit of the entire festival is the free entry for all audiences to the concert of the secondary choirs, to be held on 17 March at 14 p.m. in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The program includes the participation of the Czech jazzist Karel Rőžička and his Celebration Jazz Mass.
In the evening, the concert "Terciopel Students" will be held at the venues of the City House in Vynohrady, in which university choirs, including the choir of University Carolina, will be held.
The purpose of the Academic Festival is not only to celebrate the International Day of Students in a dignified manner and to remember the 22nd anniversary of the Third Revolution, but also to present to the public coral music at the highest level and to promote collaborative creation among young people.
The main organizer is the Czech Coral Union in collaboration with the Jan Kepler Secondary Institute.
All of the events were supported by Prague Mayor Bohuslav Svoboda and the director of Carolina University, Václav Hampl.
The Festival will take place between 16 and 20 November between Prague and Pardubice.
The calendar offers, in addition to the celebratory concerts, a whole series of musical events, improvised shows of students and morning concerts.
More information can be found on the festival page www.festaacademica.cz
