Less liquidity
Unemployment in Sinaloa during the year is multifactorial, for economist Gerardo López Cervantes, director of the U.S. Faculty of Economic and Social Sciences, the growth of unemployment can be explained indirectly, depending on the actions that have taken place since public policy.
