Interviewed about the possibility of the "vote by vote", Maria de los Angeles Llanderal explained that through the approval of the corresponding guidelines by the General Council of the EMI it will be possible to make partial and total accounts of the vote by the local electoral body.
In this way, the partial counting of votes, of one or more electoral packages, may be made on the assumption that: the results of the minutes do not coincide; there is no balloting and calculation in the box record or does not work in the office of the President of the Chamber; or, where there are obvious errors or alterations in the minutes.
In addition, the total account of the vote received in all the boxes of the election may be made where there is evidence that the difference between the alleged candidate who won the election concerned and the candidate who obtained the second place in the vote is equal to or less than one percentage point; provided that at the beginning of the meeting there is the express request of the representative of the party and/or coalition that applied for the second of the candidates identified.
The total vote may also be counted if, at the end of the ordinary term, the difference between the alleged winner and the second place is equal to or less than a percentage point, provided that there is the express request of the political party representative whose candidate remained second, in which case the electoral packages that have been the subject of partial counting will be excluded.
