There are so many I could talk all afternoon about the bassists I love.
How did Pearl Jam keep the grunt relevant even though it was no longer a fashion?
I think we all always feel a little disconnected from the word grunge.
When I think about it, it reminds me of the bands I mentioned before, such as Mudhoney, Soundgarden, Nirvana and all those that emerged at the same time, and, if there's relevance now, I think it's something wonderful because it's music that's worth listening to and bands like Mudhoney are now doing better music than ever before.
At first, his music had a darker content and has now become more positive.
What is the reason for this change?
