So was the work of the chaplain who identified the body of Alfonso Cano
A clofoscopyist from Cali passed on to history as the man who confirmed the death of "Alfonso Cano".
The work of these staff members is key.
On November 4th, a clofoscopeist from Cali's ITC passed on to history as the man who confirmed the identity of the head of the Farc: "Alfonso Cano", through the elbow of his fingerprints.
Of the seven lophoscopists working in the ITC section, that week was the turn of "availability" to Eliazar González, a man from Puerto Tejada who has been working in the judicial investigation area for 21 years.
When he began his career, González worked in the municipalities of the Chocó, where he often had to stay for more than five days in the jungle to reach the site where the corpses were to be identified.
In 2000, he moved to the capital of the Valley and, after taking the corresponding courses, specialized in hofoscopy, which is the study of friction skin, i.e. the palms of the hands and feet.
The week of the operation against alias Alfonso Cano to Eliazar warned him to wear minimum clothing for three days.
Something big was waiting for you.
On Friday night he left for the Caucasus on a helicopter from Palmyra.
He knew that he should identify two corpses and that one of them was suspected of being the man who led the oldest guerrilla in the world, so they asked him to carry Guillermo León Sáenz's decactullary card (his real name).
However, when he arrived with the research team at the site where the corpse was located, he did not recognize it because of its physical appearance, as it was very different from what he had seen in the media.
He was beardless, dressed like a peasant in the area, without glasses and much thinner.
But the prints don't lie.
Accompanied by a galtonian lens, ink, a transplanter and a flashlight, Eliasar compared the fingerprints of the corpse with those of the card.
His eye did not fail him: it was "Alfonso Cano".
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was responsible for confirming to the Minister of Defense, Juan Carlos Pinzón, that he was the chief of the Farcs.
In search of the footprint
For a disciple of the Sijín de Cali the recognition made by President Juan Manuel Santos to Eliazar González, in the press conference for the operation against "Cano", is very significant.
Many people don't know our work.
Dactyloscopy is an accurate science, without any margin of error, which can become key in solving crimes.
Apart from the identification of corpses, lophoscopists support investigations for crimes such as theft and murder and confirm the identity of the captured persons.
When captured, many criminals have fake IDs or no papers.
We take the fingerprint and search them in the database.
The investigator told him that, in a case of theft, he had to remove a piece of wall from a house, for in that place the thief had supported his hand to pull out a strong box full of jewelry and money.
"The walls are difficult because they are not suitable surfaces to extract a fingerprint, but in that case we could get the footprint from all hands and identify the offender, who had participated in different thefts," he recalled.
The fingerprints may also rule out or reaffirm suspects in cases of murder.
They recently found a dead man with bottles of liquor around him.
Through the investigation it was determined that a family member could be suspected of the crime and, indeed, a mark on the bottle coincided.
Although this does not guarantee that it was the killer, it does place it in the scene of the crime.
A CTI typologist explained that in the objects "prints are removed with chemical or physical reagents".
When they appear, a transplanter or tape is used to lift them.
After this, the impressions are sent to the Asif, which is the criminal database, or to the Registry.
"The problem is that there are still many undocumented Colombians," said the ITC expert.
He clarified that not everything is as shown in the CSI television program.
Just as not everything that shines is gold, not everything that touches becomes a mark.
However, if it can be used, if the respective rib is made.
