The arrangement adopted by the Austrian Government approaches the "German model", as Germany was the first European country to adopt such a "rule".
By 2017, the structural government deficit should decrease annually by 0.75% of gross domestic product (GDP) and, as of 2017, the structural government deficit of the Federal State should not exceed 0.35% of GDP each year, while regional States, as well as municipalities, should present balanced budgets.
The objective is to reduce public debt by around 2020/2021 under the 60% criterion set by the Maastricht Treaty.
