Democracy is a precious but also fragile good.
The European continent should be able to remember this because, although it was invented in Athens more than 2,000 years ago, throughout the 20th century it has suffered the tragedies of the World War, totalitarianisms, the Holocaust, the gulag, but also Franco in Spain, Salazar in Portugal, the crowns in Greece.
